When you create or customise a new component:

## Component
- Use [AppTemplate.vue](mdc:packages/vue/src/components/template/AppTemplate.vue) as a template
- Follow patterns from existing components in `packages/vue/src/components`
- Create a corresponding `.story.vue` file
- Vue package components must be application-independent applicable without API dependencies

## Story
- Use [AppTemplate.story.vue](mdc:packages/vue/src/components/template/AppTemplate.story.vue) as a template
- Add brief documentation as a `.story.md` file following existing documentation structure
- Avoid duplicating documentation that is already documented in the source code
- Refer to existing source code documentation instead of rewriting it
- Adjust existing stories as necessary

## Dokumentation
- Use [AppTemplate.story.md](mdc:packages/vue/src/components/template/AppTemplate.story.md) as a template
- Adjust existing documentation as necessary
